article.headline: Utah State 68, Long Beach State 52
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Spencer Nelson scored 16 points and pulled down a game-high 11 rebounds to lead Utah State University to a 68-52 win over Long Beach State Thursday night. It was Nelson's eighth double-double of the year and the 20th of his career. Nate Harris scored 15 for USU (20-7, 11-5 Big West) and Jaycee Carroll dropped in 13. The 49ers (7-19, 4-11) were led by reserve Kevin Houston with 12 points and Cody Pearson with 10. Jibril Hodges, Long Beach's scoring leader at 13 points per game, was held to five points on 2-of-10 shooting. Cass Matheus, starting for USU for the first time, scored 14 points and pulled down four rebounds. USU went on a 10-2 run to begin the second half, sparked by four points and a showy assist from Carroll. Midway through the second half, USU recorded steals on four consecutive Long Beach possessions to help extend the USU lead to as many as 27 points with 6:10 remaining. The Aggies, who are playing for second place and a first-round conference tournament bye in the Big West Conference, scored 13 of the first 15 points of the game and eventually led by 19-8 midway through the first half. But Long Beach went on an 11-3 run and got to 22-19 with 4:45 remaining after Pearson made a spinning layup. USU came into the game leading the nation in field goal percentage (54.2) and Harris ranked as the second-highest field goal percentage nationally. USU shot 52 percent Thursday night, but was only 8-of-19 from the free-throw line.
